{"lemma":"غَزْلِ","slug":"غَزْلِ","root":"غ.ز.ل","root_slug":"غ-ز-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ز-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَزْل","root":"غزل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31803","n31805","n31806"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%92%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spin"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to sweet-talk, to flirt, to cajole, to display amorous gestures"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pirouette, to whirl","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَزَلَ (ḡazala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thread, yarn","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compliment, flattery, cajolery","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"erotic poetry, love hymns; erotic poetry as a genre","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ghazal (a poetic form mostly used for love poetry in Middle Eastern, South, and Central Asian poetry)","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"amorous, erotical","tags":["rare"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31803","headword_ar":"غَزْلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to cotton, (S, O, K, TA,) and flax, &c., (TA,) or wool, and the like, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magozuwlN","text_ar":"مَغْزُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spun"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, Msb, K, TA:) [or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spun thread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yarn of any kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] it is an inf. n. used as a subst.: (Msb:) of the masc. gender: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guzuwlN","text_ar":"غُزُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  And accord. to ISd, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"web of the spider."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazolu AlnabaAti","text_ar":"غَزْلُ النَبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied in Egypt to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sort of food called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iToriyap","text_ar":"اـِطْرِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Trw","text_ar":"طرو"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n31805","headword_ar":"غَزَلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as expl. by 'Abd-El-Muttalib El-Baghdádee, in his Exposition of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqodu Al$iEori","text_ar":"نَقْدُ الشِعْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Kudámeh, signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk, and actions, and circumstances, occurring between the lover and the object of love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"differing somewhat from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiybN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a celebrating of the person and qualities of the beloved; and from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiybN","text_ar":"نَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mentioning of the state, or condition, of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsib","text_ar":"نَاسِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[himself], and of the object of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiyb","text_ar":"نَسِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of all the affairs, or events, occurring between them two, [in the prelude of an ode,] thus including the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$obiybN","text_ar":"تَشْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and being a mentioning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazal","text_ar":"غَزَل"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to Kudámeh, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inclining to foolish and youthful conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a manifesting of passionate love, and becoming notorious for affections to women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or it is the subst. from 3 [as such signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk, and amatory and enticing conduct, with women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"play, sport, dalliance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wanton conduct, and amorous talk, with women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magozalN","text_ar":"مَغْزَلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"play, sport,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversion, with women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk of young men and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or, accord. to the leading authorities in polite literature, and those who have made the language to be their study, [or rather accord. to a loose and post-classical usage,] it signifies, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasiybN","text_ar":"نَسِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praise of what are apparent of the menbers of the object of love:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mention of the days of union and of disunion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K","ISd","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n31806","headword_ar":"غَزِلٌ","root":"gzl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is, by, rule, the part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazila","text_ar":"غَزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as such signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Talking, and acting in an amatory and enticing manner, with a woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: but it is said that it] signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibu gazalK","text_ar":"صَاحِبُ غَزَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutagaz~ilN biAln~isaA='i","text_ar":"مُتَغَزِّلٌ بِالنِّسَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) by which is here meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making mention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speaking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who makes mention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who speaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in verse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazal","text_ar":"غَزَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying as expl. above, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the talk, and actions, and circumstances, occurring between the lover and the object of love;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; thus used as being a possessive epithet, [not as a part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazila","text_ar":"غَزِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this differs in meaning from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tagaz~ala","text_ar":"تَغَزَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] i. e. it signifies [properly]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uwgazalK","text_ar":"ذُوغَزَلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"displaying amorous gestures"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour, and foolish and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2256},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthful conduct such as is suitable to women, with the love,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passionate love, that he experiences for them, in order that they may incline to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kudámeh, TA:) or it is applied to a man as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a companion of women"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of his lacking strength to be otherwise: from what here follows. (IAar, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lacking strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability, to perform,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplish, things;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remiss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid, in respect to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}